This paper focuses on improving privacy protection in Web search, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a decentralized solution, which involves distributing the load among other nodes, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions handling queries separately, which involves database management (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a solution that relies on trusted execution environments (TEEs), which involves software engineering (cs.SE).
